Quality of Life Matters
Select Medical's expertise helps approximately 60,000 people in a typical day. From our specialty hospitals to our outpatient centers, we have a single goal: offering the best setting for the best outcome. Our continuum of care means we are there for our patients at every step in their healthcare journey.


Request an Appointment
Work With Us
Make A Referral
Find A Location







Long-Term Acute Care
Our specialized acute care hospitals promote recovery from the most critical and complex medical and surgical conditions. Each hospital has physicians on hand, as well as experienced caregivers including nurses, respiratory therapists and rehabilitation therapists.


Request an Appointment
Work With Us
Make A Referral
Find A Location







Medical Rehabilitation Hospital
Select Medical's highly regarded rehabilitation hospitals provide comprehensive physical medicine and rehabilitation programs and services that optimize patient health, function and quality of life.


Request an Appointment
Work With Us
Make A Referral
Find A Location







Outpatient Rehabilitation
Our outpatient clinical teams provide preventative and rehabilitative care that maximizes functionality and promotes well-being. Individualized treatment plans are developed to help achieve each patient’s specific goals. We are conveniently located in 32 states and the District of Columbia.


Request an Appointment
Work With Us
Make A Referral
Find A Location







Business Solutions
A relationship with Select Medical provides access to the nation’s top clinical and operational experts in contract rehabilitation at a national and local level.  The unique feature of our outcomes program is our ability to customize our system to meet the needs and expectations of our customers. 


Request an Appointment
Work With Us
Make A Referral
Find A Location






















Improving Quality of Life
From some of the most critically ill individuals in our nation’s healthcare system to some of the most fit athletes, our patients benefit from the combined knowledge and expertise of over 42,000 employees. No matter what the setting, our people are dedicated to providing an exceptional patient experience. This is the Select Medical Way.
As part of our commitment to a great patient experience, at least three million hours each year are devoted to tracking, reporting and analyzing quality metrics. Read about the commitment to quality as well as to the communities where we live and work in the Annual Quality and Corporate Social Responsibility Report (opens in a new window).


Our Services See All

As one of the nation's largest providers of specialized hospital, rehabilitative and outpatient care, Select Medical offers our patients a supportive and nurturing environment -- no matter where they are on their healthcare journey. 
We operate more than 100 long-term acute care hospitals, specializing in medically complex cases. Our 19 inpatient rehabilitation hospitals offer targeted therapeutic services under the direction of a physician specializing in physical medicine.
At nearly 1,500 outpatient centers, we offer physical and occupational therapy, as well as occupational medicine. Our outpatient team also provides physical therapy and athletic training to approximately 300 high schools, colleges and professional sports teams.
 





Featured Job at Select Medical See All
Chief Operating Officer-Administrator-in-Training  | Orlando, FL, Nashville, TN, and Grosse Pointe, MI
Select Specialty Hospital specializes in the care of medically complex and critically ill patients and offers a range of programs including pulmonary/vent, neuro/trauma, wound care, and telemetry. Some of our hospitals are free standing, while others are unique "hospital-within-a-hospital" models combining the personalized attention of a small hospital with the best therapeutic and diagnostic services of a large medical center. This is an exciting position and offers excellent potential for career growth in a diversified and dynamic, nationally recognized healthcare company. Qualified candidates will have 3 to 5 years management experience in acute care or specialty hospital operations. The ideal candidate will also have a strong commitment to authentic leadership, outstanding customer service and continuing program development in a dynamic and highly competitive healthcare market. Requires MHA or equivalent Master's degree and ability to relocate for CEO post upon successful completion of training. Select Medical offers excellent potential for career growth in a leading, nationally recognized healthcare company.
 










